{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Fd3qasd8HqpxVcf96T4mkD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The TLS connection is failing because the certificate doesn't have `127.0.0.1` in the SAN list. I need to add `IP:127.0.0.1` to the server certificate's SANs, or use the DNS hostname for the connection. Let me try connecting via the hostname rather than localhost/127.0.0.1.\n\nActually the issue is that `mongosh` defaults to connecting to `localhost` which resolves to `127.0.0.1` and the cert doesn't have that IP SAN. I need to either:\n1. Add `IP:127.0.0.1` to the SANs and regenerate\n2. Connect using the pod's hostname/DNS name\n3. Use `--tlsAllowInvalidHostnames` (but that defeats the purpose)\n\nThe simplest fix is to regenerate the server certificate with `127.0.0.1` added to the SAN list.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":227,"cache_read_input_tokens":34066,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":227},"output_tokens":35,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4a9db669-f470-4a3d-ad0e-e273a61bc56b","uuid":"5745d97a-ee93-4404-b6d4-c60519596461","request_id":"req_011CcQe7koXWXB3VHgtcTQwQ"}
